# HNG Stage 0 - Interactive Todo Card

A clean, responsive, and fully accessible Todo/Task Card component built for the HNG i14 Internship (Stage 0).

🔗 **[Live Demo on Vercel](https://stage-0-todo-app.vercel.app/)**

## 📌 Project Overview
This project is a single, stateful task card designed to mimic modern project management tools (like Jira or Linear). It demonstrates a strong understanding of semantic HTML, responsive CSS design, and basic DOM manipulation using vanilla JavaScript.

## ✨ Features & Requirements Met
- **Semantic HTML5:** Uses proper tags (`<article>`, `<header>`, `<time>`) instead of generic divs.
- **Accessibility (a11y) First:**
  - Fully keyboard navigable (`Tab` flows logically through interactive elements).
  - Screen-reader friendly with `aria-label`, `aria-live="polite"`, and `role="list"`.
  - Custom-styled, accessible checkbox.
- **Responsive Design:** Mobile-first layout that elegantly constrains to a maximum width on desktop and tablet viewports.
- **Dynamic State Visualization:** Toggling the checkbox instantly updates the card's visual state (strike-through text, badge updates) via JavaScript.
- **Automated Testing Ready:** All required `data-testid` attributes are perfectly mapped for automated grading.

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- **HTML5:** Semantic structure and accessibility markers.
- **CSS3:** Custom variables (Dark Mode theme), flexbox, media queries, and modern UI styling.
- **Vanilla JavaScript (ES6):** Event listeners and DOM manipulation for state toggling.

## 🚀 Running Locally
To view this project locally, simply clone the repository and open the `index.html` file in your browser. No build steps or package managers are required.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/bukola2005/STAGE-0-todo-app
# Open index.html in your preferred browser